-- в”Ђв”Ђ Affinity в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Affinity is a relationship intelligence CRM for venture capital, private equity, and investment banking teams that automatically captures email and calendar data to surface warm introductions and manage deal flow.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$custom$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Roughly 2,000 dollars per user per year, with an approximate 20,000 dollar annual minimum$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2014, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Mid-size (serves 3,000-plus customers across 70-plus countries)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$San Francisco, California, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Affinity Review: Relationship Intelligence CRM for VC and Private Equity$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Affinity is a relationship intelligence CRM built for venture capital and private equity dealmakers. See pricing, features, pros and cons, and FAQs.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Affinity is a relationship intelligence CRM built specifically for private capital dealmakers, including venture capital firms, private equity firms, and investment banks, headquartered in San Francisco and founded in 2014. Unlike general-purpose CRMs, Affinity's core differentiator is automated relationship-data capture: rather than requiring analysts and partners to manually log contacts and interactions, Affinity ingests email and calendar activity across a firm's team to automatically build a network graph of relationships, reportedly spanning more than 50 million people, without manual data entry. This lets firms see who on their team has the strongest existing relationship with a target company's founders or executives, surfacing warm introduction paths for sourcing new deals rather than relying on cold outreach. Affinity also enriches company profiles automatically with data such as funding history and revenue signals, and provides relationship scoring that ranks the strength of connections to help partners prioritize outreach. The platform is used across the full private capital lifecycle: deal sourcing and pipeline management, relationship and network management, and portfolio or investor relations tracking after a deal closes. Affinity has raised institutional venture funding itself, including an 80 million dollar Series C round, and counts investors such as Menlo Ventures, Advance Venture Partners, 8VC, and MassMutual Ventures among its backers; the company reports serving more than 3,000 customers across more than 70 countries. Pricing is not published on a self-serve basis; industry pricing references suggest costs of roughly 2,000 dollars or more per user per year, with an approximate 20,000 dollar annual minimum contract value, positioning Affinity firmly as an enterprise product for professional investment firms rather than a low-cost, self-serve CRM. It should not be confused with Affinity Photo or Affinity Designer, the unrelated creative software products made by Serif; this Affinity, found at affinity.co, is a relationship-intelligence and deal-management platform purpose-built for capital markets, venture capital, and private equity workflows, competing with tools like DealCloud, Pitchbook's CRM features, and Salesforce-based deal-tracking implementations customized for finance.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '14315019-5fc0-4f79-b27c-b60ee1c1017e';

